      "id": "22032021_d7f33405",
      "file_path": "cps-application/pom.xml",
      "patchset_number": 17,
      "line": 41,
      "message": "For now, it is possible to build the application by having the base integration image in the local registry and keeping `docker.repository.pull` value empty.\n\nThis will not be possible anymore with this change that requires to have a value for `docker.pull.registry`.\n\nBecause of that, it seems that I'm not able to build the application anymore in Bell env as the proxy is blocking the connection to onap pull registry.\n\nI'm curious about how other Bell team members are building locally and if they are still able to build the application using Bell proxy, with this change.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 5658,
